main event: A bright light was observed moving with great speed for approximately 4-5 seconds over the Norton Sound area.
interesting points: The object was approximately 1/4 the size of the moon.
The object exhibited a slow, jerky eastward motion.
The observer, Barker, was unable to conclusively identify the object, but ruled out satellites, astronomical phenomena, and normal aircraft.
The overall reliability of the source is considered poor.
The report mentions an AGENA-11 satellite that was observed at the same time, but it's unclear if this was related to the unidentified object.
